<p>A possible addition to this list: a TV tends to force (or correlate with) a less social arrangement for living rooms. In the vast majority of living rooms with a television, all seating is facing the television, a setup that makes it difficult for people to focus easily on one another. It&#8217;s something that has always bothered me.</p>
