<div class="format_text" id="comment-body-18021">
<p>After lightening hit close to our house in June 2007 and fried every piece of electronics, we decided to NOT replace the TV. For nearly two years we were TV-free &#8212; even with two little kids. It was the BEST thing we ever did because our children were free to create, to explore and to learn without the compromising influence that television programming brings. Even now with three kids, we have one television but no cable. I truly believe we are happier because we are able to apply our time pursuing more fulfilling activities. Thanks for the great post! Be well!</p>
