<p>It seems very popular these days to jump on the TV is evil bandwagon. Maybe it is.  can understand these points, and agree with some of them, but agree that they can be applied to things other than TV. What about mindlessly surfing the internet? I waste more time doing that than TV. And if I read at the end of the day I&#8217;m reading fiction for entertainment, not instructive nonfiction.</p>
<p>Plus sometimes by the end of a long day I want to just sit back and relax. I don&#8217;t need more time to work or &#8220;get things done,&#8221; I do enough of that already. I need to refresh and relax each day as well, and a good show or movie provides that for me. I already exercise daily, cook and eat at home, spend time with friends and others, and work all day.</p>
